  "title": "DIGITAL PRODUCT  MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Job description</p><p>Product managers play a key role in ensuring that food and beverage products are not only delicious, but also safe, compliant, and meet the needs and preferences of consumers.</p><p>Product managers in this industry must keep a pulse on the latest market trends, regulatory requirements, and consumer preferences in order to develop products that meet and exceed customer expectations.</p><p>Finally, understanding consumer preferences and demands is critical for product managers in the food and beverage industry. Consumers today are more health-conscious and environmentally aware than ever before, and they expect the products they buy to reflect these values.</p><p>Duties and Responsibilities</p><p>•\tidentifying the key market segments and trends that are driving growth and innovation</p><p>•\tstay up-to-date with the ever-changing regulatory landscape. With the rise of food safety concerns and the increasing demand for transparency</p><p>•\tcompliance with food safety regulations is more important than ever</p><p>•\tMeeting with the sales and marketing team to discuss digital marketing strategies.</p><p>•\tDesigning and implementing online marketing strategies across all digital platforms.</p><p>•\tManaging the company’s social media platform and web advertising.</p><p>•\tDeveloping social media strategies.</p><p>•\tIdentifying the latest trends and technology within the industry.</p><p>•\tAssessing the online user experience and developing strategies</p><p>•\tMaintaining customer communications with weekly reports, news articles, and industry guides.</p><p>•\tMonitoring and maintaining the media budget.</p><p>•\tPreparing and presenting digital marketing reports.</p><p>Requirements and Qualifications</p><p>•\tIn-depth knowledge of F&B related products.</p><p>•\t Experience with social media networking and advertising.</p><p>•\t Ability to work well under pressure.</p><p>•\tKnowledge of the latest technology and trends within the industry.</p><p>•\tGood interpersonal skills.</p><p>•\t Strong communication and presentation skills.</p><p>•\t Detail-oriented with strong organizational skills.</p><p>•\t Ability to conduct thorough research.</p><p>•\tAbility to work independently and as part of a team.</p><p>•\t Strong problem-solving skills.</p><p>•\tWillingness to stay updated on industry trends.</p><p>•\tExperience in training and mentoring staff.</p><p>•\tDegree or Diploma or minimum three years relevant work experience</p><p>•\tAble to work early mornings, nights, and weekends</p><p></p><p></p>",
